  shortDescription: A framed photo from our wedding day, 1979. Robert in his father's
    too-short tie.
  fullStory: 47 years of marriage. The day they promised forever, not knowing what
    forever would mean.
  marthaContext: Martha remembers Robert's nervous hands, how he fumbled with the
    ring. She held his hands steady then, just as she does now.
  davidContext: "David was the best man. He remembers the toast he gave \u2014 something
    about Robert being the bravest coward he'd ever met."
